11/07/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The government has started work on reforming the country's electoral system, cabinet spokesman Christos Protopappas said Thursday (10 July). 
Ministers are to meet next week in a bid to make the system more transparent. 
Protopappas invited all political parties, especially the main opposition New Democracy, to participate in the process. 
(ANA, MPA - 10/07/03)
